---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import fs from 'node:fs/promises';
import path from 'node:path';

const allowedSlugs = [
  'commute-cost-calculator',
  'remote-vs-office-calculator',
  'remote-pay-adjuster',
  'meeting-cost-calculator'
];

const registryPath = path.resolve('tools/registry.json');
const registryData = await fs.readFile(registryPath, 'utf-8');
const registry = JSON.parse(registryData);

const tools = await Promise.all(registry
  .filter((entry: any) => entry.status === 'active' && allowedSlugs.includes(entry.slug))
  .map(async (entry: any) => {
    const defPath = path.resolve(`tools/definitions/${entry.slug}.json`);
    const defData = await fs.readFile(defPath, 'utf-8');
    return { ...entry, definition: JSON.parse(defData) };
  })
);

tools.sort((a, b) => a.priority - b.priority);
---

<Layout title="Remote Work & Commute Economics | Econified" description="Calculate the hidden costs of commuting, evaluate remote salary cuts, and value your time." canonicalUrl="https://econified.com/tools/remote-work-economics/">
  <main class="container">
    <nav class="breadcrumb" style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <a href="/" style="color: inherit;">Home</a> &rsaquo;
      <a href="/tools/" style="color: inherit;">Tools</a> &rsaquo;
      Remote Work & Commute
    </nav>
    <div style="text-align: left; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      <h1>Remote Work & Commute Economics</h1>
      <p class="lead">The uncompensated time and cost of commuting is massive. Use these tools to see if a remote job with a lower salary is actually the better deal.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="glass-panel" style="margin-bottom: 3rem; line-height: 1.7;">
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">The Hidden Math of Commuting vs. Remote Work</h2>
      <p>When employers offer remote positions at a 10-15% pay cut, most people focus on the salary reduction. But they rarely calculate what commuting actually costs. A typical 30-minute one-way commute costs $8,000 to $15,000 per year when you include fuel, vehicle depreciation, parking, and the time value of the hours spent driving. A 60-minute commute can exceed $20,000.</p>
      <p>This means a remote job paying 10% less can actually put more money in your pocket if it eliminates a moderate commute. The break-even point depends on your specific costs, which is exactly what these tools calculate.</p>

      <h3>Geographic Salary Arbitrage</h3>
      <p>Remote work also creates the opportunity for geographic arbitrage — earning a salary benchmarked to a high cost-of-living city while living somewhere cheaper. A software engineer earning a San Francisco salary while living in Austin, Texas effectively gives themselves a 30-40% raise in purchasing power. However, many employers now adjust pay based on location, making the real advantage smaller than the headline suggests.</p>
      <p>The <strong>Remote Pay Adjuster</strong> tool helps you calculate whether a location-adjusted remote salary is still better than a local office job when you factor in commute savings and cost-of-living differences.</p>

      <h3>The Meeting Tax</h3>
      <p>Remote work changes how time is spent. Without a commute, you gain 1-2 hours per day. But remote teams often fill that time with meetings. Research suggests the average knowledge worker spends 31 hours per week in meetings, and each unnecessary meeting has a calculable cost based on attendee salaries. The <strong>Meeting Cost Calculator</strong> helps quantify this so you can make the case for fewer, shorter meetings.</p>

      <h3>Which Tool Fits Your Situation?</h3>
      <p>Start with the <strong>Commute Cost Calculator</strong> to understand your current commute's true annual cost. Then use the <strong>Remote vs Office Calculator</strong> to compare a remote offer against your current in-office position. The <strong>Remote Pay Adjuster</strong> handles location-based salary adjustments, and the <strong>Meeting Cost Calculator</strong> helps evaluate the productivity side of remote work.</p>
      <p>For the complete methodology behind commute cost calculations, read our guide on <a href="/guides/commute-true-cost/">how much your commute really costs</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Remote Work & Commute Tools</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem;">
      {tools.map((tool: any) => (
        <a href={`/${tool.slug}/`} class="glass-panel" style="display: block; text-decoration: none;">
          <h2 style="color: var(--accent-light); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.25rem;">{tool.definition.title}</h2>
          <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">{tool.definition.description}</p>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
